title: Joseph Brothers Tree of Life Hand Wrapped Sea Abalone Shell Earrings for Women, French Wire Antiqued Copper
description: Basic information
Earring Size: L - 2 1/4" , W - 7/8" Earring Weight: 0.4 oz (12 grams) / pair Earring Material: abalone shell, antiqued copper wire Earring Making: Hand wrapped
Production

This tree of life earring is made by high quality copper wire and strictly selected abalone shell. Every piece of mop is polished into perfect drop shape in size 12 x 20 mm. shaping the tree is the most challenge work. The whole process is done by hand with a plier. The life tree not only has to be wrapped tightly on the shell, but also looks beautiful and the proportion shall be harmonious.
About abalone shell
Abalone shell is called "sea opal", which displays beautiful array of iridescent rainbow colors with hints of green, blue and red. Not like other MOP, it's color is strong and unique for every piece.
About tree of life

Based on Celtic traditions and beliefs, tree of life brings you good health and lucky. title: Memento Mori Copper Reminder Coin
description: The long history of "Memento Mori" reminders includes coins. We have added our own spin on the concept and included a new reverse side, “Memento Vivere” which translates to “remember that you have to live.” We believe there is a beautiful balance between accepting mortality and embracing life. Memento mori (Latin: "Remember that you have to die.") is the medieval Latin Christian theory and practice of reflection on mortality. Especially as a means of considering the vanity of earthly life and the transient nature of all earthly goods and pursuits. Memento vivere (Latin: "Remember you have to live.") Know that your time is short in the grand scheme of things. So have fun while you are here. This solid copper coin is about 1/2 ounce, or 30 grams of solid bullion grade pure copper. We have chemically and manually aged the coin so the patina looks great right out of the package and will look even better with more wear from handling and daily carry. The product is treated to look as if it has been handled and circulated. This process is done by hand, and it is both an art and a science, coloring and patinas will vary. No two are exactly the same! Coins are struck one at a time in the USA using antique machinery and traditional coining techniques. Original coin art by Michael Shantz Shire Post Mint. All rights reserved.

description: IMPORTANT CAUTION !! - When ordering 2 barrettes, the quantity selection should be 1. The quantity means one set or one pair. This listing offers a set of 2 solid leather hair barrettes in your choice of design and the color brown or black. These oval-shaped barrettes are hand-made in Mooresville, Indiana, USA. We have been crafting these heavy-duty leather barrettes for nearly 50 years now. There are four design options as well as plain. We have two different floral designs that we label Floral #1 and Floral #2. We also offer a unique Paisley pattern and Peacock feather design. The photos represent the design choices, but please understand that leather is a natural substance and each barrette will be unique. Each piece of leather will take the dye in its own way, and therefore there will be some variations of the colors. Each oval-shaped barrette is 2" tall and 4 1/4" wide. The centers of the holes are 3 1/4" apart. The barrette sticks are made of lathe-turned hardwood, very sturdy, and finished in an attractive dark stain. We sometimes hear, "Oh, I can't wear those. My hair is too thin." Or, "Oh, I can't wear those. My hair is too thick." NOT TRUE!! If your hair is long enough for a ponytail, you can wear our barrettes. Just put your hair up into a ponytail with an elastic hairband. Then add the barrette by spearing the stick just above the hairband. You do not have to surround all of your hair and the barrette can't slip off because it is trapped by the hairband. The barrette covers the hairband, making it look as though you are only wearing the barrette. If you want to put your hair up in a bun, put it in a low ponytail first. Then twist your hair up and add the barrette.

title: Screaming Aztec Death Whistle - Carnivore
description: Our handmade Aztec Death Whistles produce the loudest, most ear piercing screams you will ever hear from a whistle. They recreate a human scream in both pitch and decibel level that has to be heard to believe.   How they are made: These whistles are not cheap toys, nor cheap souvenir items you can pick up on vacation. Made of high grade resin and epoxy, we hand make each whistle one at a time here in our Florida based studio. We create the whistle component separate from the design and then embed the whistle into the design of your choice, so any design you choose will sound great. We also supply 1 yard of a leather/suede cord so you can hang the whistle around your neck looped through the back of the whistle, or use it to hang on display. History: If you are unfamiliar with an Aztec Death Whistle read about the history: Death whistles were first discovered in Mexico hundreds of years ago in the burials grounds of the Aztecs. Often the whistles were found clutched in the bony fingers of a skeletal corpse. Historians believe the whistles were used in sacrificial rituals of death, as a number of whistles were found with sacrificed victims to the Aztec wind God Ehecatl. Other theories propose that the whistles were used in war to strike fear in the hearts of their enemies. Imagine hundreds of whistles blowing in all directions as the Aztecs descend on their adversaries.

title: Gifts of the Magi Three Wise Men Handmade Glass Christmas Ornament, Gifts for the Birth of Christ
description: The smallest ornament on your tree will have the greatest meaning. Handmade in the USA Bring back the true meaning of Christmas with our exquisitely crafted ornament featuring genuine 23k gold. The three gifts of the Magi, the most valuable items of the ancient world, are beautifully displayed in an antique style glass bottle, ready to hang on your Christmas tree, wreath or garland. Each ornament is handmade one at a time, and will arrive beautifully packaged in a keepsake box. An information card is also included Ornament Size: 2" x 1/2" (not including hook)  The story of the three wise men and their gifts were illuminated in Matthew 2:11, "... and when they were to come into the house and they saw the young child with Mary his mother, and fell down and worshiped him: and when they had opened their treasures, they presented unto him gifts of Gold...." The gifts of the Magi represented the most valued items of the ancient world for the birth of Christ.  The first gift, brought by Mechior of Persia, is Gold. Valued as currency, it was also the gift given to kings. It is the easiest to identify of the three gifts. Its radiance and beauty was also used in jewelry and other sacred objects.  The second gift brought by Gaspar of Arabia, is an aromatic gum from the Middle East and Africa. It was used in medicines, perfumes and incense, and as an anointing oil with which the priests were consecrated.  The third gift, brought by Balthasar of Ethiopia, is a dark reddish brown gum from a small spiny tree found in the Northeast Africa and Southern Arabia. It is mentioned several times in the bible for its medicinal uses, and it was the oil that anointed Jesus' body before his burial and offered to him on the cross in wine to relieve his pain.

description: The Perfect Gift

This custom star map print makes the perfect piece to mark any significant life event, be it a birthday, wedding, anniversary, "day we met," and more. See the sky as it was at that very moment your life changed. Your star map will show the stars exactly as they were at that location on that date--and even that time, if you wish!
Customer Service
We pride ourselves in providing the highest level of customer service. Our goal is to make sure you are satisfied and love your print, as evidenced by our reviews.
Superior Paper Quality

All prints are created with high-performance, 100% cotton-based, bright white matte paper with a velvety linen texture. After sourcing multiple brands and types of papers, we’ve found that our cotton paper gives an exceptional final product, exhibiting photo-quality images without the use of lesser-quality photo paper.
Customizations

All text is customizable, based on options entered prior to adding this item to your cart. The default quote on this print is "and it was then that the stars did align" but this can be customized. Because this is a fully customized piece of art, the number of stars, visibility of the Milky Way, and other features of the sky will vary based on the date/time/location of your star map.
Quality Assurance

No part of our processing is outsourced. From the reception of the order, to processing, printing and shipping, we handle it all. You will also have the opportunity to approve a proof of your print prior to shipping.
Unframed
We do not offer framing because we found that frames suitable for shipping do not meet our quality standards. Instead, we offer standard-sized prints to make finding the perfect frame easy.

title: Genuine Raw Moldavite Pendant in a Wire Prong Setting-Stainless Steel-Sterling Silver-Copper-Bronze-14K Gold or Rose Gold- Necklace or Choker-Czech Moldavite, W/Cert. Of Authenticity
description: This is a beautiful raw moldavite pendant from the Czech Republic that has been set in a handmade wire prong setting of your choice that holds the moldavite in place from behind while displaying the front without any obstruction. All moldavites used for this piece will be between 0.75ct and 1.5ct, being roughly the same size and shape as the moldavite pictured above. This is real Genuine Czech Moldavite, and will vary in color and size due to being a natural stone. As this is a production piece, each moldavite will be slightly different and housed in a cage hand wrapped to look just like the one in the picture. Measurements: Length: 0.75-1.00" "Width: 0.25-0.50"Depth: 0.25-0.50" This elegant but minimalist setting helps to accentuate the natural beauty of this otherworldly stone, creating a true showpiece. About Moldavite: A product of a meteor strike that took place in the Moldau Valley in what is now the Czech Republic more than 14 million years ago, Moldavite is a olive green tektite that was formed from the impact created by the heat and kinetic energy of the meteor striking the sand, creating a special type of gemstone that has some of the properties of desert glass, but others that are unique, with flecks of the meteor itself strewn throughout the stone. Moldavite is as incredibly rare as it is beautiful and is thought to be a powerful stone sought after by healers for its strange resonance and properties as well as gem enthusiasts around the world. All of our moldavite jewelry comes with a Certificate of Authenticity and is not made into jewelry until we have performed our own tests here at the shop. This is for the pendant only, if you want a necklace, upgrades are available. Please DO NOT Shower, Bathe, Swim, or bring this piece into contact with water or caustic chemicals. Please cleanse the metal part with appropriate jewelry cleanser for the stone type.
